sql:
SELECT * 
   FROM invoice_items 
   WHERE sale_amount > (SELECT AVG(sale_amount) FROM invoice_items);

SELECT region_id, COUNT(*) AS NumberOfInvoices
FROM sales_summary
GROUP BY region_id;

SELECT SUM(sale_amount)
FROM invoice_items
WHERE stock_code = '1';

external_knowledge:
- "voyage leaders" refers to customers;
- "journey" refers to their overall spending through invoices;
- "golden threshold" metaphorically refers to the $1000 total expenditure mark.

- 'shining stars' metaphorically refers to customers with many orders;
- 'purchasing journeys' metaphorically refers to the process of making orders/invoices;
- 'from the beginning of winter in 2022 until the first frost of 2023' refers to the period from January 1, 2022, to December 31, 2022;
- 'how many times did they dazzle us with their orders' metaphorically refers to the total number of orders or invoices.
